om politics, the book suggests a new and progressive agenda for white working class communities to become a fully inclusive part of a modern and diverse country in the 21st century. The book will be valuable to academics and students as well as policy-makers and practitioners in national government and organisations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMulticulturalismzGreat Britain. 0aPrejudiceszGreat BritainvCase studies. 0aWhite peoplexRace identityzGreat Britain. 0aWorking classzGreat Britain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Services & Welfare.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015z97831111964280 cprintz978144731396040uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447313977?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447313977zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447313977/original  a978-3-11-119642-8 Bristol University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA